B28 - Produce a cyber safety flyer for Uni students

Objective
the goal of this activity is to create an educational cyber safety flyer to raise awareness about common cybersecurity risks and safe online practices

Method
i designed a simple cyber safety flyer aimed at university students, focusing on common threats and best practices for staying secure online

Findings
the flyer includes the following key cybersecurity recommendations:
1. use strong and unique passwords - avoid reusing passwords across multiple accounts to reduce risk of compromise
2. enable multi-facto authentication - adds an extra layer of protection beyond just a password
3. be cautious of phishing attacks - do not click suspicious links or provide personal information through unknown emails or messages

Security principle
this activity reinforces key cybersecurity principles:
- confidentiality
- authentication
- awareness

Evidence
- flyer in evidence folder

Reflection
this activity helped reinforce the importance of cybersecurity awareness in everyday life. many security breaches occur due to user behavious rather than technical failures, so educating users about safe online practices is an effective way to reduce risk.
